    short: 'Roll 1d10 + STAT + SKILL and meet or beat a DV (or the opposing roll) — a single d10, never a d20.',
    body: 'Everything resolves the same way: **1d10 + STAT + SKILL + modifiers**, compared to a **DV (Difficulty Value)** or to an opponent\'s roll.\n\nMeet **or beat** the DV and you succeed. A Handgun 6 Solo with REF 8 rolls **1d10 + 8 + 6**, so they hit a DV 15 on anything but a natural 1 — competent people in this game are genuinely competent, and the d10 is a small swing on top of a large fixed base.\n\nThat is the crucial structural difference from a d20 game. Your **stat + skill** is usually **10–18** and the die is **1–10**, so **who you are matters more than what you roll**. There is no proficiency bonus scaling in the background; the number is just the number.\n\nTwo things break the pattern, and they break it hard:\n\n· A **natural 10** **explodes upward** — roll again and add.\n· A **natural 1** **explodes downward** — roll again and subtract, and it is a **Critical Failure**.\n\nWhen two people directly oppose each other — a Facedown, a grapple, sneaking past a guard — both roll the same way and **the higher total wins**, with ties going to the higher **stat**.',
