    term: 'DV',
    kind: 'term',
    short: 'Difficulty Value — the number your 1d10 + STAT + SKILL must meet or beat. The common ladder is 13/15/17/21/24.',
    body: '**DV (Difficulty Value)** is the target number. Meet or beat it.\n\nThe standard difficulty ladder:\n\n· **Everyday** — **DV 13**\n· **Difficult** — **DV 15**\n· **Professional** — **DV 17**\n· **Heroic** — **DV 21**\n· **Incredible** — **DV 24**\n\nMany tasks have their own published **DV tables** rather than a vibe-based number — this is the part of the system that most resembles a reference manual. Ranged attacks are the big one: each weapon type has a **DV per range bracket**, so a Very Heavy Pistol at 0–6m is a different DV than the same gun at 25–50m. You look it up; the GM does not invent it.\n\nOther things with their own DV tables: **driving** manoeuvres, **Netrunning** actions against a NET Architecture, **First Aid** and **Paramedic**, **Demolitions**, and the **Trauma Team** response.\n\nBecause STAT + SKILL is typically 10–18, a **DV 13** is nearly automatic for a professional and genuinely uncertain for an amateur. That is the design: DVs sort the trained from the untrained far more than they create drama for experts.',
