    short: 'A natural 10 on the d10 EXPLODES: roll another d10 and add it to the total.',
    body: 'Roll a **natural 10** on your d10 and it **explodes upward**: roll another **d10** and **add** it to your total.\n\nSo a natural 10 gives you **10 + (1–10)** on the die alone, before stat and skill — a range of **11 to 20** from a single d10. That is what lets an amateur occasionally do something extraordinary, and it is why no DV is ever strictly impossible.\n\nThe second die does **not** explode again. You roll once more and that is the end of it — no infinite chains.\n\nThis applies to **any** check: attacks, skills, opposed rolls. It does **not** apply to **damage** rolls (those are d6s and have their own critical rule) and it does **not** apply to the **Death Save** (which is a roll-under against BODY, where a 10 is simply the worst possible result).\n\nNote what this is not: there is no "critical hit" doubling of damage from a natural 10. A natural 10 makes you more likely to **hit**; the separate **Critical Injury** rule governs whether the hit was catastrophic.',
