    body: 'Roll a **natural 1** and the die **explodes downward**: roll another **d10** and **subtract** it from your total.\n\nA natural 1 therefore contributes **1 − (1–10)**, a range of **−9 to 0**. A Solo with REF 8 and Handgun 6 who rolls a natural 1 and then a 9 ends up at **14 − 9 = 5**, and misses a shot they could not otherwise have missed.\n\nAs with the upward version, the **second die does not explode again**.\n\nA natural 1 is also a **Critical Failure** in the fiction, and the GM is entitled to attach a complication on top of the arithmetic: the gun jams, the tool slips, the lie lands wrong, the vehicle fishtails. Some subsystems have explicit fumble tables (Netrunning and driving in particular).\n\nThe important consequence for play: **nobody is ever safe**. A 10% chance of the floor falling out means the ganger with a cheap pistol can genuinely embarrass the corporate hitman, which is exactly the tone the system wants.',
