    short: 'Ten stats rated 2–8 at creation: INT REF DEX TECH COOL WILL LUCK MOVE BODY EMP. Added directly, no modifier table.',
    body: 'Cyberpunk RED has **ten STATS**, each rated **2–8** at creation (humans cap around **10** in play, and some cyberware raises them).\n\nThere is **no modifier table**. The stat is **added directly** to the roll — STAT 8 means **+8**, not +3. This is why a starting character is already good at their job and why the d10 rarely overturns a gap in competence.\n\n· **INT** — Intelligence: perception, education, deduction, Netrunning\n· **REF** — Reflexes: shooting, initiative, dodging, driving\n· **DEX** — Dexterity: athletics, melee, stealth, brawling\n· **TECH** — Technique: repairing, building, medicine, picking locks\n· **COOL** — Cool: nerve, persuasion, interrogation, resisting a Facedown\n· **WILL** — Willpower: resisting torture, concentration, resolve\n· **LUCK** — Luck: a **spendable pool**, refreshed each session\n· **MOVE** — Movement: how far you go per Move Action\n· **BODY** — Body: melee damage, HP, carrying, and the **Death Save**\n· **EMP** — Empathy: reading people, conversation, and the visible face of **Humanity**\n\nBuilding them: the **Streetrat** and **Edgerunner** templates hand you an array; **Complete Package** point-buy gives you a pool to distribute, minimum **2** and maximum **8** in any stat.\n\nTwo stats are unlike the others. **LUCK** is a currency you spend down. **EMP** is not really yours — it is **Humanity ÷ 10**, and it drops every time you install chrome.',
