    short: 'Physical toughness: it sets your HP with WILL, your melee damage, and it is what you roll under on a Death Save.',
    body: '**BODY** is the stat that decides whether you live.\n\nThree jobs:\n\n· **Hit Points** — **HP = 10 + 5 × (the average of BODY and WILL, rounded up)**\n· **Melee and Brawling damage** — your damage dice come off a **BODY table**, not the weapon: BODY 4 is 1d6, 5–6 is 2d6, 7–10 is 3d6, and 11+ is 4d6\n· **The Death Save** — while **Mortally Wounded** you roll **d10 and must come in UNDER your BODY**, with a cumulative penalty\n\nThat last one is why BODY is not just another stat. A **BODY 8** character survives Mortal Wounds that kill a **BODY 4** character outright, and no amount of skill compensates.\n\nBODY also governs carrying capacity, resisting being knocked down or grappled, and how much armor you can wear without penalty.\n\nCyberware — **Grafted Muscle and Bone Lace** and the like — can raise BODY, which is one of the two reasons Solos chrome up. The other reason is that they are shot at frequently.',
