    short: 'Empathy: reading and connecting with people — and it is simply your Humanity ÷ 10, dropping as you install chrome.',
    body: '**EMP (Empathy)** is the only stat you do not fully control, because **EMP = your current Humanity ÷ 10, rounded down**.\n\nEvery piece of **cyberware** you install costs **Humanity**, and each full **10 points** of Humanity lost takes **1 point of EMP** with it. Chrome yourself to Humanity 39 and your EMP is **3**, permanently, until you get therapy.\n\nEMP is the parent stat for the skills that make you a person: **Conversation**, **Human Perception**, **Interview**, and the social read that tells you someone is lying. A low-EMP character is not just bad at talking — they are **visibly wrong** to other people, which the GM should play.\n\nAt **Humanity 0**, EMP reaches 0 and the character is lost to **cyberpsychosis** and becomes an NPC.\n\nThis is the central bargain of the whole game and it runs in one direction: the chrome that keeps you alive on the street is the thing that stops you being someone worth keeping alive. Every Solo is spending EMP to buy REF, and the bill always comes.',
