    body: '**LUCK** is a stat and a currency at once. Your LUCK rating is the size of the pool.\n\n· **Spend Luck points BEFORE you roll**, one at a time; each adds **+1** to the check.\n· You may spend as many as you have, on any check.\n· The pool **refreshes completely at the start of each session**.\n\nThe timing rule is what makes it interesting: you must commit **before** seeing the die. You cannot look at a 4 and buy your way to a 15. So spending Luck is a bet on how badly you need this particular roll, made in ignorance.\n\nUse it on: the shot that has to land, the Death Save arithmetic you want to survive, the DV 17 you cannot otherwise reach, the Facedown you cannot afford to lose.\n\nUnlike **Humanity**, Luck comes back — and unlike stress in other games, it costs you nothing but itself. It is the one unambiguously generous mechanic in Night City, which is presumably a joke.',
