    short: 'One Move Action plus one Action per turn — no bonus actions, no reactions. Trade the Action for a second Move.',
    body: 'Each turn you get exactly:\n\n· **1 Move Action** — travel up to **MOVE × 2 metres**\n· **1 Action** — attack, use a skill, operate something, run a Netrunner turn\n\nYou may **swap your Action for a second Move Action** to sprint (**MOVE × 4m**, doing nothing else).\n\nThat is the complete action economy. There are **no bonus actions**, **no reactions**, **no free object interactions**, and **no attacks of opportunity**. If it is a thing, it costs the Action.\n\nThings that cost your Action: firing a weapon (single shot, or **Autofire**, or a **Suppressive Fire** burst), an **Aimed Shot**, a melee attack, First Aid on a friend, hacking, jacking in, drawing *and* firing in the same turn if the GM is strict about it.\n\n**Dodging bullets** is not free — it requires the **Evasion** skill and, for gunfire specifically, a REF **8 or higher** to even attempt. Most people simply get shot at and rely on their **armor**.\n\nOne round is roughly **3 seconds**. Combat is short and it is decisive.',
