    body: '**Initiative = 1d10 + REF**, rolled **once** at the start of combat. Highest goes first, and that order **holds for the whole fight** — you do not re-roll each round.\n\nThat single roll is why **REF** is the most valuable stat in Cyberpunk RED. A REF 8 character with a good roll acts before everyone, every round, for the entire fight — and in a game where a Very Heavy Pistol does **4d6** into a **35 HP** body, acting first is frequently the entire fight.\n\n**Cyberware** buys initiative directly: the **Sandevistan** and **Kerenzikov** speedware boost initiative or grant extra actions, and they are among the most expensive **Humanity** costs in the book for exactly that reason.\n\nThe **Solo\'s Combat Awareness** Role Ability can be spent on **Initiative Reaction**, adding to the roll — one of the ways a Solo simply refuses to lose the first round.\n\nTies go to the higher **REF**; if that ties too, roll off.',
