    short: '1d10 + REF + weapon skill vs a DV read off the weapon\'s range table — the DV rises with distance.',
    body: 'Shooting is **1d10 + REF + the weapon\'s skill** (Handgun, Shoulder Arms, Heavy Weapons, Archery) against a **DV read from the weapon\'s range table**.\n\nThe DV is not invented — every weapon type has a published row of DVs by **range bracket** (0–6m, 7–12m, 13–25m, 26–50m, 51–100m, and out). A pistol at 6m might be **DV 13**; the same pistol at 50m is far harder. **Look it up.**\n\nModes of fire, each costing your **Action**:\n\n· **Single shot** — the default\n· **Aimed Shot** — **−8** to the roll, but you pick a **body location**; a hit on the **head** does **double damage** after that location\'s armor\n· **Autofire** — uses the **Autofire** skill (a ×2 skill); a hit multiplies damage by the margin, capped by the weapon\'s autofire rating\n· **Suppressive Fire** — no damage; forces targets in the area to keep their heads down\n\nDamage is a **flat dice value per weapon** — a Very Heavy Pistol does **4d6**, an Assault Rifle **5d6** — with **no stat added**. Then **armor Stopping Power subtracts**.\n\nYou cannot dodge bullets without **REF 8+** and the **Evasion** skill. Everyone else takes it on the armor.',
