    body: 'Melee is **1d10 + DEX + Melee Weapon** (or **Brawling** for fists), opposed by the defender\'s **Evasion** or against a DV the GM sets.\n\nThe unusual part is damage: it comes from a **BODY table**, not from the weapon.\n\n· **BODY 4 or less** — **1d6**\n· **BODY 5–6** — **2d6**\n· **BODY 7–10** — **3d6**\n· **BODY 11+** — **4d6**\n\nA weapon then modifies or replaces this — a **Very Heavy Melee Weapon** does more, **Cyberarms** and **Wolvers** have their own values — but the baseline principle stands: **how hard you hit is about how big you are**, not what you\'re holding.\n\nA **Martial Arts** skill (a ×2 skill) unlocks special moves and better damage than raw Brawling.\n\nMelee reaches **2 metres**. Grappling, choking, and throwing all resolve as opposed BODY-based checks. And melee damage runs into **armor SP** exactly like a bullet does — punching a Solo in a Metalgear jacket accomplishes nothing.',
