    term: 'Hit Points',
    kind: 'term',
    short: 'HP = 10 + 5 × (the average of BODY and WILL, rounded up) — typically 25–45, and it never grows with "levels".',
    body: '**HP = 10 + 5 × (the average of BODY and WILL, rounded up)**.\n\nBODY 6 and WILL 5 average to 5.5, rounds to **6**, so **HP = 10 + 30 = 40**. BODY 4 and WILL 4 gives **HP = 30**.\n\nMost characters live between **25 and 45 HP**. That is the whole range, forever. **HP does not scale** — there is no level, no hit die, no per-level HP gain. A character who has survived a year of campaigns has exactly the HP their BODY and WILL say they have, and an Assault Rifle still does **5d6**.\n\nThe two thresholds that matter:\n\n· **Seriously Wounded** at **half your maximum HP or below**\n· **Mortally Wounded** at **0 HP or below** — Death Saves begin\n\nRecovery is slow and medical, not magical: you heal HP per day of rest based on BODY, faster with a successful **First Aid** or **Paramedic** check, faster still in a **Trauma Team** bay or a cryotank. Nothing in this setting brings back the dead — **Trauma Team** just gets there before you finish dying, if you paid the subscription.',
