    short: 'Rated in Stopping Power, which subtracts from damage and ablates as it takes hits. There is NO armor class.',
    body: 'Armor in Cyberpunk RED is worn **by location** — **head** and **body** each have their own armor and their own **SP** — and it does exactly one thing: **subtract from damage**.\n\n**It never affects whether you are hit.** There is **no armor class** here. A Solo in a Metalgear is just as easy to shoot as a naked civilian; the bullets simply do not accomplish much.\n\nThe common armor ladder by SP:\n\n· **Leathers** — SP 4\n· **Kevlar** — SP 7\n· **Light Armorjack** — SP 11\n· **Medium Armorjack** — SP 12\n· **Heavy Armorjack** — SP 13\n· **Flak** — SP 15\n· **Metalgear** — SP 18\n\nHeavier armor imposes a **penalty to REF, DEX and MOVE** — Metalgear makes you a slow, invulnerable target, which is a real trade.\n\nIf you wear two layers, you use the **higher SP** and take a penalty; you do **not** add them together.\n\nArmor **ablates** — every hit it stops wears it down — and it can be repaired with **TECH**. **Subdermal armor** and **Skinweave** cyberware give SP that cannot be shot off, at a Humanity cost.',
