    term: 'Armor-Piercing',
    kind: 'term',
    short: 'AP ammunition halves the target\'s SP (rounding up) and ablates it by 2 — but does less damage once through.',
    body: '**Armor-Piercing (AP)** ammunition is the answer to Stopping Power, and it costs you something for the privilege.\n\n· It **halves the target\'s SP** for that hit, **rounding up**. SP 11 Light Armorjack becomes **SP 6**.\n· It **ablates** the armor by **2** instead of 1.\n· But the round does **reduced damage** once it has punched through — you trade raw stopping force for penetration.\n\nAgainst an unarmoured target, AP is strictly worse than a normal round. Against **Metalgear (SP 18 → 9)**, it is the difference between a firefight and a waste of ammunition.\n\nThis is the arms-race the setting runs on. Armor gets heavier; ammunition gets smarter; the Solo carries two magazines and has to guess which fight they are walking into.\n\nOther specialist ammunition exists on the same principle — **Expansive** does more damage but is stopped cold by armor, **Rubber** is non-lethal, **Incendiary** and **Biotoxin** have their own effects. They are all **per-shot** decisions that cost eddies.',
