    short: 'Roll two 6s on the damage dice: +5 damage that IGNORES armor, plus a rolled lasting injury.',
    body: 'The nastiest rule in the combat chapter, and it fires off the **damage** roll rather than the attack roll.\n\nIf **two or more of your damage d6s come up 6**, you have inflicted a **Critical Injury**:\n\n· **+5 damage**, and that 5 **bypasses armor entirely** — SP does nothing against it\n· **Roll on the Critical Injury table** for the body location you hit\n\nThe injuries are lasting and specific — **Foreign Object**, **Broken Ribs**, **Broken Arm**, **Collapsed Lung**, **Damaged Eye**, **Concussion**, **Whiplash**, and at the head end, things that end careers. Each carries its own ongoing penalty and its own **DV to treat** (some need **surgery**, not a First Aid check).\n\nThis is why **more damage dice** matter more than the average suggests. A **5d6** Assault Rifle has a far better chance of showing two 6s than a **2d6** SMG, so heavy weapons are not just louder — they are structurally more likely to cripple.\n\nAnd it is why armor does not make you safe. **SP 18 Metalgear** stops the bullets and does nothing whatsoever about the +5 and the broken ribs.',
